place_description: Espresso drinks, light fare & sweet treats offered in a modern, laid-back space with patio seating.

reviews_data.review_text: Really enjoyed this coffee shop. Highly recommend  they also sell caramel drizzle and white chocolate.

I love this coffee shop and have been coming here for years. However, a recent visit was ruined by the customer service. My wife has a lactose allergy while breast feeding our newborn. If she consumes dairy the baby will spit up all of her milk. Asking for an allergy menu isn't weird but when we asked for one the woman taking our order responded "we don't have that but we do our best." We can't just hope that your "best" is enough to ensure our little one won't get sick from her food. We'd rather just take our business somewhere else with makes me sad.
Great coffee and danishes, especially the cream cheese!

Coffee shop that serves up food, coffee, smoothies, tea, and ice cream. Seasonal flavor options are available. Staff is friendly and willing to make recommendations. I typically like to get an iced mocha so I can compare businesses. The iced mocha here comes with whipped cream and was very good!
Insanely good coffee, very rich and flavorful. Fair prices.
Beautiful place.
Good coffee and pastries, staff is always nice.
This is one of my go to spots to work away from home with great coffee and a Christian atmosphere

This is the Harrisburg coffee shop. The parking lot can get a little hairy, but that's because this is the place. I wouldn't complain if there was more seating, but I adore RRCC and will continue to patronize them regularly.
Great little place
The breakfast items, frappes and mochas here are fantastic. I'm in here about every week and have no complaints. The staff is very friendly and so are Kyle and Dave as owners.

I recently visited Rocky River Coffee Co. for my weekly Cafe Friday outing, and I had a great experience! The staff was super friendly, my bagel was delicious, and my matcha was just right. It's a cozy spot with a local feel, but seating can be limited--there's an extra room in the back, but sometimes it's booked, so keep that in mind. The cafe does get pretty busy, but parking is shared with other businesses in the shopping center and was easy to find. If you're looking for a great coffee spot with a welcoming vibe, I definitely recommend stopping by!
Good food, good coffee

The cutest little coffee shop!! The employees are always smiling and courteous, and patient while I decide what I want. The baked goods are sooooo delish! Best coffee cake I've ever had, and their apple danish is also amazing. I hear they make a lot of them in house to! delish!! They have a really good selection of beverages. Also a really cute place to hang out and study or work. They have a whole side room with tables/chairs, and also comfy chairs that you can use. Highly recommend if you want a good cup of coffee and a nice atmosphere. Ooh and they also have ice cream which my daughter loves!

I drove all the way to this place to get my hands on their famous skillet brownie, but to my dismay, they were out of it. The server recommended the skillet cookie, which I agreed to, even though she informed me that it would take 20 minutes to warm up the oven. She reassured me that it would be worth the wait, but I ended up waiting for 45 minutes. When I went to check on the order, I found out that the server hadn't even turned on the oven. When I questioned her about it, she claimed that she wasn't aware that I was waiting. This is unacceptable. I had even ordered a beverage to enjoy with my dessert, which I ended up drinking by itself. I am extremely disappointed with this experience, and I will never come back to this place.

Coffee was just ok. Barista gave us both a mocha (I ordered a regular latte). Barista and staff were a bit chatty which is fine but I'm sure the distraction caused the order screw up. I drank the mocha - it was imbalanced and had way too much sugar which overshadowed the coffee (flavor).
I did order the chocolate peanut butter cookie tho. That was pretty amazing and unique - almost like a pressed crumbly biscuit with oats in it maybe? I could eat a ton of those.

Service was pretty slow; there was some argument about making a cortado a customer behind us requested.. barista said they don't make them (pretty sure because they didn't know how to make one ).
Have went twice this past week. The coffee and breakfast sandwiches are great. 10/10 would recommend!!
Best cappuccino I've had in a long time! Also, delicious muffins (the blueberry one is the best!) and the attention was very nice !
THE BEST MATCHA!!! I love everything about this place the pastries are DELICIOUS and the drinks are the perfect amount of sweetness. Top cafe in NC tbh
Wow everything we ordered was DELICIOUS. The NY bagels the crumb cake the coffees. So good will be back!!
Not a ton of seating but the coffee is good.
I love this place. Good coffee, good food, good prices. I've been making random appearances since high-school and I'm never disappointed.

We come in pretty regularly, but the service was awful today. After waiting a while for coffee order to be made, they gave the order to someone else. Instead of apologizing and jumping on a replacement, that resulted in yet another long wait. The final straw, after all that, was having the audacity to ask for .25 cents for a water. Do better.
great place, but if youre wanting an iced caramel latte definitely get the SALTED iced caramel latte
It's not that great. Needs updating.
Great coffee. Can get cramped inside when it is busy.
Been here twice so far, the food and coffee is very consistent. Great employees and everything. One of our favorite coffee spots.
Loooove their coffee! Workers are always so sweet and everything I've had on the menu is so good!

My favorite coffee shop. Delicious lattes. A limited but scrumptious menu of sandwiches. My favorite ice cream. All surrounded by kind people who want to make your experience enjoyable. I shouldn't tell you because I'd love to keep this place a secret just for me.
Always a pleasant experience when visiting the coffee house. Great tasting coffee, good breakfast sandwiches, and delicious pastries! I am quickly trying to become a regular!
Great little coffee shop!
Great coffee and atmosphere.
Stopped on road trip for afternoon snack and coffee break.  Got cappuccino, cold brew, oatmeal creme pie, and lemon blueberry loaf slice for less than $20.  All tasted great.  Comfy seating area.

Exactly what you would want from a local coffee shop. Great friendly service, great coffee and baked goods.

The atmosphere is perfect with space to relax, chat, or work both inside and out.

Good pricing with medium mocha frappe with two shots for $5
My favorite coffee shop!!!! I love everything service , coffee, ice cream, cookies, bagels , muffins, and everything!!

Stopped here on a friend's recommendation.  This places HITS!! Had a bacon, egg n cheese biscuit and the rocky rivet milkshake (a shake with espresso in it).

Everything was amazing and the girls behind the counter were very nice! Will definitely be back!!

Cozy little coffee shop that has a good variety of drinks. I like the Rocky River in the summer time. I get it with coffee ice cream and it's refreshing on a hot day. They also have a good selection of seasonal drinks so be sure to check out the current specials they have.
Nice cozy shop with a private seating area, and helpful staff. The coffee/tea is sub-par, but the atmosphere is good and makes for a pleasant working/studying environment.

I placed a to-go order over the phone for a blueberry muffin and latte... BEST. DANG. MUFFIN. EVER.

The latte was also excellent and the ladies were very nice when I came to pick up my order! 12/10
I wasn't overly enthusiastic about my coffee, which took 6 minutes to make even though I was the only person in the store. The coffee wasn't particularly good or bad.
Best coffee ever.
It's not Starbucks, and that's a good thing! Staff are wonderful too.

Meh. It's not a 'real' coffee place. Seems like untrained young adults that would rather be anywhere but there working. They don't know basic things like when to add a double shot per request, nor general drinks. Ordering takes a while for this reason and waiting for the drink...yikes.. plan to wait forever once the order has been made.

Definitely room for improvement, but given how long it has been in business, seems this is as good as it gets. Reminds me of a place that just learned about electricity back in the early days and is just getting up to speed ...

Not a fan of all the PAID/FAKE reviews either. That's super cringe and disingenuous.

LOCAL GUIDE=PAID/FAKE REVIEW. 98% of them are all local guide reviews.

I'd go back if there was new management and a grand reopening.

Hope there's some serious improvement. Would love to have a GREAT coffee spot in that plaza.

Sure! Here's a review for you:

---

I recently visited Rocky River Coffee and had a fantastic experience. I ordered a large Caramel Macchiato and a sausage and egg croissant, and both were absolutely delicious. The Caramel Macchiato was rich and flavorful, perfectly balancing the sweetness of the caramel with the robust coffee taste. The sausage and egg croissant was fresh and savory, with a buttery, flaky croissant that complemented the hearty filling. The ambiance of the coffee shop was cozy and inviting, making it a perfect spot to relax and enjoy my breakfast. I highly recommend Rocky River Coffee for anyone looking for a great coffee and breakfast experience.
Nutella Frappuccino on top
Great local coffee shop that has been a go to spot for early morning coffee and sandwiches with friends. Has a great atmosphere with some regulars and their $1 coffee with their travel mug is great.
Great atmosphere, pleasant staff and awesome owners!
Our party had coffee and ice cream. Both were delish! Coffee actually tastes like coffee here and the ice cream is creamy and tastes great. Prices are awesome too  .

I love this place! The coffee, the food, the feel, the layout. Everything!
The coffee was spectacular! (I got my usual latte)
I also got a bacon breakfast burrito which was exquisite- crispy bacon, eggs, no superfluous fillers.
They have a ton of seating in a number of areas so you can have a good chat, read a good book, or get some work done!
They even have some outdoor seating.

This place is at the top of my list to visit again! Next time I'll try a pastry!

Great place and all but if you are going to be working with food and drinks, wear a hair net as well as gloves. To that woman that let her child behind the counter while she worked, disgusting. We don't know where he's been or where his hands have been or what he's touching. The owner Dave replied and told me to take my business elsewhere which I will gladly do. Just because that child is your son doesn't mean he has the right to be behind the counter. You don't know what I look like or what my real name is. So you don't know who it is. Are you going to ban all of your customers?  Responding to Dave again, my profile isn't fake. Grow up, you're a business man. You're so pathetic. Also you don't know who I am. If you do please oh please tell me who I am. I can assure you, you'll be wrong.
Great coffee
everyone at this Cafe goes above and beyond, but I want to especially thank Natalie and Peyton for always greeting me with a smile and making my day

Let me tell you what you want to know. Bakery items are displayed in glass to the right of the counter, seating options are moderate, and prices are comparable to other cafes. Coffee for two will probably run you $12-$14 depending on your tip. Selections and taste wise, it's pretty comparable to any other cafe minus a cortado on the menu (missed that). What makes this cafe unique though is in their level of personalization. You can really tell they care about each customer's experience from the friendly conversation to attention to detail. Overall you've got my recommendation Rocky River Coffee!

Insider Tip: If you'd like a more set aside hang out setting try the back room open to customers past the counter and pastry display. It has a few tables set up and is perfect for homework, studying or intimate conversation.

This is a great coffee shop, with good coffee, good food, and very friendly people working there. They prepare drinks quickly, but the place has an unhurried, relaxed atmosphere on both sides of the counter.
THE BEST COFFEE!

I absolutely Love the Hot cocoa and the coffee, I tried the s'mores hot chocolate and it was so good  they have muffins that are moist and delicious. My husband had their coffee and it was very good not bitter like some just wonderful flavor. I would definitely recommend this place. The employees were all so inviting and nice

Super cute coffee spot with excellent bagels! Their lattes are amazing (highly recommend their vanilla and lavender syrups) as well as their breakfast sandwiches. Great variety and quality, especially at such reasonable prices!
Delicious as always!

NYC coffee snob here Been coming here for over a year now. Did didn't initially like the young gossipy unfocused staff but I suppose they were post Covid hires. The staff has improved now to a degree. Things like garbage bins should be put out for customers to use. Not sure how you could miss that. However the speed of service has improved a lot.
I don't like their super bitter plain coffee BUT they make a very good basic hot latte with milk. What they really excel in is their egg and cheese on a hard Keiser Roll. It's the best in Concord/Harrisburg.
They also offer delicious Blue Bell ice cream year round also.
Seating inside can fill up quickly also.
Parking can be a little tight in their small shared lot.
The people, atmosphere and coffee are awesome here.  The Wi-Fi however is very unreliable and drops every hour or so which is extremely frustrating when studying and working.
Everytime I go they are super nice and work fast! They make my drink right every time as well!
Coffee was delicious and the atmosphere was cozy! B
I love this coffee shop! Great drinks every time, and I love their breakfast sandwiches as well. Bagels and croissants are to die for
Great coffee, obsessed with the "Rocky River" which is espresso mixed with ice cream. I have this once every several months and it's such a sweet treat every time. Highly recommend.

I visited at the recommendation of a friend and found a warm, welcoming coffee shop with a bevy of cheerful and knowledgeable baristas, a menu board of any possible combo of tea and coffee that I might desire, and a case loaded with baked delights.  I've had a lot of chai tea lattes, but I can tell you that the "dirty" chai latte this morning was by far the best I've ever had.  I'll be back and you should go!
This is my favorite coffee shop by far. Always great customer service and delicious coffee and food!
Stopped to get coffee for my wife.  She like her "good" coffee.  She really enjoyed her hot latte (can't remember the flavor).
Great coffee and great customer service!
Great place to get delicious coffee and hang out with friends and family. Very relaxing atmosphere. Food's not bad either.
Reminded me of Tate St. Coffee in Greensboro: same relaxing, down to earth atmosphere. Good coffee. Gracious staff.

Fantastic coffee. We got Jack Frost (seasonal peppermint and white chocolate) and Nutty Irishman lattes - the flavors were perfectly balanced with the coffee. Delicious! Side note: There were some random teen couples making out, but that's not the coffee shop's fault. Youths.
First time visiting.   Beautiful quaint little coffee shop.  Atmosphere was very welcoming.  The brown sugar latte with oat milk was everything.
Great place for coffee, I always get the frappes, have been going there for a few months now.
Loved it here will be coming again
Love meeting friends there or going by myself!

Rocky River Coffee is great. This is the first time we've been here. There is handicap parking. I use a walker. The store is easy to get to, and easy to get around in. We went on a Sunday afternoon. It was busy, but they were fast with our order. Our coffees were excellent and very hot. The cookies were almost more than one person could eat. We'd like to go back again
Stopped here while staying in the area and had the best coffee and morning atmosphere. Definitely will go back!
My boyfriend and I always come by here for a mini date. We love to get our smoothies and coffee here! Always a nice stop.

Absolutely amazing experience at this coffee shop, their tea is incredible and their coffee is good. Their coffee flavors are extremely strong and their sandwiches are delicious. Definitely will stop by again
Wonderful place to hangout and enjoy iced coffee outside with sidewalk tables and chairs. Music was at a perfect level and peaceful.

One day I randomly came to Rocky River Coffee Co. while waiting for my food next door and it was love instantly! The workers are always so friendly and helpful. The coffee shop is always so clean and welcoming and the coffee and food are to die for every time!
Best coffee shop around!!

Highly recommend the Old Harrisburg room for small get togethers! Very affordable and delicious lunch for everyone that came.

Great place! Can't believe I've been driving by here for 4 years and never knew it existed.

I ordered the special strawberry mocha frappe and the caprese panini and both were delicious!

Great atmosphere. Perfect for working. Will totally be back!

Kids loved the ice cream, the pasty selection looked delectable however the coffee was mediocre. If you're in the business of coffee you should know about your roast and how to properly execute an espresso whether it's the traditional Italian style or an American macchiato.

I'm traveling visiting family in Concord NC and discovered this coffee shop. I've come here almost everyday for the whole two week stay. The coffee is amazing. There are so many options to choose from. Favorite is the Iced Vanilla Lavender oat milk Latte. The pastries are absolutely amazing and the atmosphere is so cozy  and has the perfect coffee shop vibe. Staff is also super friendly! Wish I had a spot like this back home in Massachusetts.

I absolutely love this place!!! I am visiting my brother and working remotely. I came here a few times to work. I would give this place a 10/10 for food, service and atmosphere. Also best latte's I have had near Concord.

Consistently top notch service and great atmosphere. The baristas are always friendly and helpful. The owners go the extra mile and care about their customers. You won't find a better combo of quality product and excellent service anywhere. Highly recommend!

Thought it was rude the barista's father to come in and harass her for awhile. Before I knew he was her father, it looked like a strange man harassing her the entire time. So, I said something about it. I would rather be wrong and say something than right and not say something. Anyways, he told me he's her father and he's allowed to harass her. My response was it's unprofessional since nobody else knows that he's her father. Just an upset man bothering her the entire time. He had a group of men with him, as they were leaving he passively and in a snarky way told the guys "she doesn't know how to make specialty drinks"- as they were walking passed me. So obviously it didn't seem like he was her father, why would a father act like that in her work of place? "Harass" her in the appropriate environment. On her break, at home, wherever. He had 3 people behind him as he was at the register and she had to tell him there are people behind him that need to order... just a bit unprofessional and irritating that he would be doing this.... Anyways, this is for management to do and say something about it. I feel bad for the girl. She's doing her best.
This is a great place

Very small and cute coffee shop. Worth the walk! Both times i've gone there were a good amount of people in there so it feels lived in. Prices are good too which is always something that can be annoying local coffee! Would definitely support over a national chain!!
Breakfast sandwich trash
Completed
I love this place
Great food, coffee, and place to get some work done.

It offers a pleasant cafe experience with a charming ambiance. As a coffee lover, I thoroughly enjoyed their Dirty Chai Latte, which delivered a rich and satisfying flavor. The coffee cake was a standout, delighting the taste buds with its delicious sweetness. While the Egg and Cheese Panini had a good taste, it was a bit oily for my liking. As for the Mango Frappe, it fell somewhere in the middle, not impressing greatly but not disappointing either. Overall, It provides a pleasant atmosphere and enjoyable coffee options, making it a recommendable spot for a coffee lover seeking a cozy cafe experience.

What a charming little coffee shop! Very nice and relaxing atmosphere. Good food and great cup of coffee   There's more to this charming little place such as smoothies, ice cream, tea, etc. Also, if you need to rent out a business meeting room this place has one! Had a really nice time here overall.
Wife's happy she got herself a good ice coffee
Blue bell ice cream!.amazing...soo good and th price is below average ..you will love the environment.

Rocky River was absolutely delicious. I got the crossiant sandwich and the crossiants were buttery and flaky. They were so good. I also got a Rocky River drink, I thought that was a clever invention and it was delicious as well.
Nice place to relax enjoy some coffee with friends
Got some half and half iced tea and an apple Danish. Enjoyed the atmosphere and friendly folks.
Best coffee  Shop in Harrisburg!  Amazing & friendly staff and soothing environment to enjoy & lounge.
Best coffee around with a great environment made for working and studying
Staff is consistently angry and bad customer recovery.
This is one of my favorite coffee shops in the charlotte area. I just wish they would switch to decomposable cups and lids.
Came in from out of town and the coffee was great. People are friendly and the owners went out of their way to treat me as a local. Keep up the excellence!
The large hot caramel latte with 2% milk is very good.  It's also very hot.
Nice place around concord area, coffee tastes really good!
I can't remember ever being disappointed in a drink from here. And I certainly can't say that from many Starbucks experiences. It's such a great local spot!

This is by far the best coffee shop! The staff is really friendly. The coffee is great, along with the bakery items. Also, the perfect environment to study, meet up or hang out. I traditionally pick my favorite items, the Caramel Frappe and Apple Danish. While my children go for the ice cream!
Great breakfast and coffee pit stop while on my way into the office. I love the small town feel and sense of community here. It's also a perk that they sell smoothies and ice cream for the kids!
This is a very nice little coffee shop with great coffee and tasty treats.
Service here is hit or miss. And their coffee isn't so great either. Their food on the other hand is pretty good.
I got the coconut latte & sausage, egg & cheese on ciabatta. Everything tasted amazing; would highly recommend!
I was visiting a friend in NC, and we went here every morning! Coffee was outstanding, and the cookies were delicious. I brought one home with me!

I just stopped to get a cup of coffee. They have a lot of (food) menu options as well as drinks. It's better than Starbucks. Give them a try. You will be satisfied. There are a lot of people who have already figured this out. There was a crowd.
Great local coffee social spot, always an amazing experience.
Baristas were very helpful in suggesting a drink, friendly staff and delicious menu
Great location and prices and a large selection of drinks as well as bakery items and bagels.

My husband and daughter are regulars here. Since they convinced me to go I see why.

They don't offer soy milk, but they have other non dairy options for coffee. I chose almond milk.
I also tried an Apple Danish. It was sweet so I folded it in half. The soft bread made it perfect for me. I'm a fan.

This place is alright. I've been trying to find new coffee shops and this place looked promising but there always seems to be an issue. They don't call names when an order is ready, so it can be super confusing to pick up your drinks or food.
The last time I was here the barista barely filled up my drink, I ordered a medium and it was barely filled.
Best coffee around!
Great customer service!

This place was so good I went three days in a row (love supporting local small businesses). I have gotten the carmel macchiato with oatmilk and whipped cream. It is always just the right sweetness.  They also have very tasty breakfast sandwiches, just make sure you get there to order sandwiches before 2pm when the kitchen closes. I can't wait for warmer weather to try some of their icecream! Don't forget to ask the cashier about the rewards program.
Great tasting coffee! Great customer service!
Good taste and very good customer service
I love this coffee shop! Great choices and in a great location.

Went today for the first time and I was content with my breakfast sandwich and caramel frappe. I did wait a little long for both items. Moreover, a few of us did get an order update after waiting about 10 mins. Overall, satisfying visit.
Great atmosphere. Good service. Good frappes and espresso, nice panini and bagels too
First visit. Had regular coffee, spiced cider and breakfast. Loved it. Had the same issue with the tops not staying on the cups. Size small.
Delightful coffee shop. Customer  service was on point and very friendly.
Oh my gosh ! Delicious coffee!! I loved the Iced Caramel Machiato !
Best Chai around!

I'm sad to write this review because I truly love Rocky River Coffee Co. However, the last few times I've visited, a few of their younger employees had been lacking in the customer service department. Things such as not greeting customers with a smile or making them feel welcomed, looking unhappy or annoyed to be there, using no manners (you're welcome, thank you, or even a "sorry for making you wait"), gossiping to other employees behind the counter, and just really having no sense of self-awareness. I have to believe a lot of this is probably related to immaturity and a lack of training. I get this isn't a 5-star restaurant, but the employees here could definitely do a better job of being more friendly to their customers and acting professional in the workplace.

Amazing coffee, pastries, and bagels. Only downfall is cups with weak lids. If you barely squeeze your cup, or try and pick your cup up from the cupholder, be ready for the lid to come off, and a mess to clean up. Aside from that, best place within miles for coffee and grub

My sister and I have been coming here for years. We ended up moving to Ohio but every time we come back to the area we have to visit like we are today. Absolutely love this place, nothing like it in Ohio near where we live.
Where community meets... for coffee, food and conversation.
Best coffee and customer service in town. Support local!!
Always the place to go for good coffee!
Love the iced caramel macchiato with oat milk. They also have a really tasty pina colada.
Happy with quality of coffee and service! Like gem in Harrisburg vs so many other franchises
Best real coffee house vibes

I absolutely loved this coffee shop!
As a flight attendant, I visit at least one new shop per week and this local shop made top 5!
Fair prices & the quality was great.
There are many syrup flavors- sugar free and regular.
The breakfast and lunch menu make this a one stop shop.
I got an iced americano half decaf with sugar free chocolate macadamia nut & white chocolate
I also had the smokehouse Turkey hot sandwich, I will be back for this again!
They also have an outdoor seating area + a back room for privacy

Don't display items for sale if you don't really want to sell them! Walked in asked about Vanilla syrup...found a bottle on the shelf and was told.. sorry I can't sell it to you because I'm not sure if it's the last one in the store.. she said she was told that was the protocol.. many times I have walked into a store and bought the last of something that was on the shelf. If you don't want to sell it put it with your stock in the back but you should never tell a customer they can't buy something you have on the shelf displayed.. I'm not one of those people but it made me feel some kinda way if you catch my drift!
The brownie skillet was awesome and the service was great.
Cuzzy spot

I don't actually get coffee there but we get coffee there every Saturday morning after working out. The only complaint I hear about this place regularly is they are slow when it comes to making food. It has been that way for years. It's just ridiculously slow. However people keep going back so they must keep going back for a reason.
Update for Owner: The labor issue can't be the reason it has been this way for years. I hope y'all the best, I definitely am rooting for y'all! Hopefully the feedback is helpful.

Love this place. The baristas are very friendly, drinks are always great, and their baked goods are awesome. The owner, Dave, is very responsive and is a caring business owner. He is willing to go the extra mile to make sure his customers are satisfied.
Cute coffee shop! I'll be back for sure. I had the dirty iced chai....awesome...my husband had the salted caramel coffee and he loved his too.
Pleasant staff and good coffee.

I'm a regular at this coffee shop but have recently started going there less due to the quality. Got a sausage, egg, and cheese sandwich this morning and it's completely burnt. I don't know how they expect anyone to eat this lol

Cute local coffee shop. I got a salted caramel latte and it was awesome. My adult kids each got a frappe which they said were very good too. Very friendly atmosphere and quick service. They were pretty busy but I was still served quickly. Prices were good too!
Delicious pastries and coffee was perfect! New to the Harrisburg community and this is my favorite place so far.
Good place it needs new door though
Cute and delicious! We got ice cream, coffees, and cookies and everything was perfect. Nice outdoor space as well!
Cinnabon Mocha - is by far my new favorite. This coffee shop is a hidden gem and I can not wait to try more flavors in time. There pastries are delightful. Wonderful atmosphere and friendly service!
I came to this store for the ice cream...delicious!

Nothing wrong with it, nothing that remarkable either. Decent coffee, a bit slow, average prices. Certainly not something to avoid, but I wouldn't go out of my way either. A competent latte, though the pulls were slightly under-extracted. Prices were average and staff was friendly.
Yummy lattes and muffins. Cute place with good seating (indoor and out)
Great service. Food was good too. Nice place to work as well if you work remote.
Excellent coffee and muffin. Fast, friendly service.

I absolutely love this coffee shop to me 100% better then Star Bucks. I get the Mocha Frappe and everything bagel with bacon egg and cheese. The bagles are NY bagels. Just absolutely delicious . The staff is so welcoming and kind and friendly. So are customers. They have comfortable seating and tables if is a group or if your alone on your laptop. This is my favorite eatery. Try them and you will see.

I popped in around 11:30 on a Saturday and the place was popping. The line was a bit long but I waited and was rewarded for my patience. The iced latte was delicious- not too weak or watery, not bitter- just right. I grabbed an apple danish to go with it and the pastry was fluffy and light, the apples sweet but not overbearing. Overall a wonderful tasteful adventure. Will definitely come back!
Absolute gem of a local coffee shop. Not too pricy, rocking coffee, and tasty food. Haven't tried their ice cream yet, but it's probably as good.

Awesome place for coffee. Been here a number of times....quite frankly amazed I never posted a review until now. Today we had the nutty Irishman hot, it was great! I also had an egg and cheese everything bagel. It was good.

I wish I pictures from inside, it is nice and cozy. There is some outside area too.if you like coffee, breakfast, or snacks swing on by!

Went in this morning to try it, and I wish I hadn't. This place is a joke--it's not a New York bagel. It's a cheap shop ran by girls. I ordered a bagel with vegetable cream cheese, not toasted. I got a plain bagel with plain cream cheese--toasted. I came in to get it fixed and they said they didn't have vegetable cream cheese--why wouldn't you tell me that when I ordered??? I asked for a refund and they gave me cash. They couldn't give it on card. When the girls called for someone to help give a refund, she yelled to her and the response was "what?! I'm busy!" Classy. Please do NOT go to this place. If you want a real bagel, go to Mike's Bagels. Way better. Which is where I ended up. Never again.

In response to the owner's tasteless response: It makes sense why the customer service is lacking here--he clearly has zero inkling of what customer service should be. Instead of taking accountability,  he blames the problem on the customer and says there's no way the business would've lasted--news flash: the government had been in business much longer and they're still garbage.
Love the Christmas music and their winter specials are delicious. Super cozy and the staff is friendly.

We've recently made Rocky River Coffee Co our weekend place to go for coffee/sweet treat whenever we find ourselves driving through Harrisburg. Their rotating flavored coffee selections are a must try when you want something more than plain, black coffee. Also, the chocolate chip cookies are amazing.

I was out running errands and decided to grab a cup of coffee.   A quick search from Concord and passed over the coffee shop chains as I wanted a more local shop.

Sitting here I'm taking it all in, the Christmas music, the holiday decor, and the staff conversing with customers.

I would definitely recommend checking this place out if your in the mood for a great cup of coffee experience.

A Sunday morning stop for a breakfast burrito, iced chai and iced coffee to go.  The staff was super-friendly and lightning fast, except for the food.  Our drinks were ready and waiting before we even finished paying.  The iced chai was good however, it was pre-made so the options to change the milk didn't exist.  They use skim milk which was okay but I would have preferred almond milk and I heard someone else ask for oat milk.  I suspect if they started allowing the customization then they would definitively sacrifice speed.

My iced coffee was like a ninja was hidden among ice cubes, launching a full on assault in your mouth when taking a drink.  This is a powerful drink that had the potency of espresso but the flavor of cold brew coffee.  I like it, a lot but it was a very interesting explosion of flavor and intensity.  I feel like I won't sleep for four nights.

The downside of RRC is the speed of the food preparation.  To their credit, a disclaimer is hung over the pick up section that mentions they are not a fast food restaurant, food is made to order and to be patient.  We ordered two breakfast burritos, one with sausage and one with turkey, a customer behind us ordered a breakfast sandwich then a third customer was told the wait would be 30 minutes for food.  We waited about 15 minutes for our burritos and there was no one in front of us.

The burritos tasted really good and were nice and fat.  I would not order the turkey burrito again; it was cooked fine but I wasn't a fan of the taste.
